title: ‘Our Differences in Age and Skin Color Meant Nothing to Us.’
content: Constance Collins and Matthew Steuer, 24 years her senior, met five years ago as each was about to begin a teaching job in Africa.

title: ‘I’m Your Man’ Review: Living Doll
content: Dan Stevens plays a dreamy, pleasure-driven android in this delightful near-future romance.

title: An ‘Accident of Geography’ Was the Start of Forever
content: Though Valeria Dueñas and John Garfinkel come from very different parts of the country, they bonded instantly at a Washington bar — and plan to name their dog after one, too.

title: Tim Cook Faces Surprising Employee Unrest at Apple
content: Hundreds of current and former Apple workers are complaining about their work environment, a rarity for the once tight-lipped company.

title: Roger Michell, Director of ‘Notting Hill,’ Is Dead at 65
content: He was an accomplished theater director as well as a filmmaker. But he was best known for his blockbuster romantic comedy starring Julia Roberts and Hugh Grant.

title: Republican Review of Arizona Vote Fails to Show Stolen Election
content: The much criticized review showed much the same results as in November, with 99 more Biden votes and 261 fewer Trump ones.

title: Supermodel Linda Evangelista Says Cosmetic Procedure Left Her ‘Disfigured’
content: The ’90s-era supermodel said side effects from a fat-freezing procedure caused her to become depressed and turned her into a recluse after “not looking like myself any longer.”

title: Does My Mask Protect Me if Nobody Else Is Wearing One?
content: Masks work best when everyone in the room has one on, but you’ll still benefit from masking up even when those around you aren’t.

title: Gwen Ifill Was Right About ‘Missing White Woman Syndrome’
content: I’ve seen it happen time and again. Missing white women and girls receive outsize media coverage when other missing people receive none.
